{"ts":"2026-06-26T16:12:54.210Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Import Strategies**\n\nI've discovered the `motion` package now exports through `\"motion/react\"`, which is great, as it aligns perfectly with Next.js 15+ and React 19. My current focus is on deeply reviewing the task requirements so I can formulate a clear strategy.\n\n\n**Designing the Architecture**\n\nI'm now diving into the design phase. I've formulated a narrative focused on \"Sovereign Engineering & Algorithmic Certainty\" for the shared frontend tool architecture. My visualization leans towards a \"enterprise blueprints studio dashboard\" aesthetic. I'm focusing on low-light, premium interfaces, clean bento layouts, and modular, composition-based layouts. Specifically, `ToolPageShell` will wrap the tools with a consistent premium context.\n\n\n**Defining Component Hierarchy**\n\nI'm now detailing the individual components for the tool's user interface. I'm prioritizing `ToolHero` for a high-end editorial header. I'm focusing on layouts like `ToolStepLayout` for progress maps, and `ToolResultPanel` to showcase outcomes. I want to build out options with `ToolOptionGrid`, and clean input controls with `ToolInputGroup`.\n\n\n**Outlining Implementation Details**\n\nI'm now detailing some important interactive components. I'm planning a `ComparisonRail` for side-by-side spec comparisons with custom hover rows, and I'll create `ToolDataCard` for premium key-value telemetry data. Regarding interactions, I'll use Framer Motion, with subtle transitions, a spotlight card hover effect, state transition animations, and step transitions. For mobile, I'll ensure full responsiveness with collapsible sidebars, wrap-around grids, sliding tabs, and optimized touch inputs, while also focusing on high accessibility. Finally, I'll create `types.ts` and `build-services.ts`, plus interactive tool components in `components/build` or `components/inner-pages`.\n\n\n**Clarifying Task Scope**\n\nI'm now clarifying the scope of this work. I need to know if I'm tasked with updating the `/build/*` pages to use these new components, or if the requirement is solely focused on building the shared architecture for the tools. I've re-read the task details and will ensure the focus is only on the frontend, and avoiding backend integrations. I will ensure consistency, premium design, and product-grade feel for the /build tools. I will avoid duplicate systems and only create the necessary files.\n\n\n**Defining Type Structures**\n\nI'm now detailing the TypeScript types needed for the project. I've compiled a list: industry, company size, AI journey, data readiness, priorities, assessment answers, ROI inputs, proposal inputs, sandbox agent, marketplace agent, and generated local reports. I plan to create `components/build/types.ts` for these, alongside `components/build/services.ts` for local calculations and a dedicated component folder. I'll evaluate if the `/build/*` pages can leverage these improvements or be integrated. I'll focus on type, service, then component creation.\n\n\n**Detailing Service Helpers**\n\nI'm now detailing the service helper calculations. I'll focus on local, deterministic computations, avoiding network calls or fake outputs, clearly labeling previews. This involves: Assessment calculations, ROI computations, Proposal generation, Sandbox simulations, and Marketplace recommendations, all based on user inputs. I'm excited about the possibilities this opens up.\n\n\n**Defining Mock Data Strategies**\n\nI'm now establishing deterministic mock data strategies. I'm focusing on perfectly typed mock data based on input parameters, removing randomness for mathematical derivation. I will create `components/build/types.ts` and `components/build` for types, services, and components, prioritizing type design. I'm excited about `Industry`, `CompanySize`, `AIJourney`, `DataReadiness`, and `Priority` types.\n\n\n**Refining Data Structures**\n\nI'm now refining the data structures, specifically the types. I'm focusing on `AssessmentAnswers`, `ROIInputs`, `ProposalInputs`, `SandboxAgent`, and `MarketplaceAgent`. I want to ensure each structure precisely represents the data needed.\n\n\n**Defining Report Types**\n\nI'm now detailing the structure of the `GeneratedReport` type. It will include an ID, title, timestamp, report type (ROI, assessment, etc.), summary, an optional score and savings estimate, recommended steps, and metadata. I need to be sure the report summary is both informative and accurate.\n\n\n**Calculating ROI Formulas**\n\nI'm now detailing some service helper functions. I've formulated precise ROI calculations, including gross and net savings, and ROI percentages. I'm also planning resource allocation breakdown based on user priorities. The proposal generation function will create custom project names and estimate implementation timelines.\n\n\n**Designing Component Interactions**\n\nI'm now designing the interactive components to enhance the user experience. The `ToolPageShell`, `ToolHero`, and `ToolStepLayout` are coming together well, and I'm planning to introduce the `ToolSidebarProgress` to track completion. I'm excited about how the deterministic mock data will drive insightful preview calculations.\n\n\n**Defining Component Library**\n\nI'm now detailing an extensive library of interactive components. I'm focusing on `ToolStepLayout` for progress visualization. I will craft a dynamic `ToolResultPanel` for showcasing results with premium hover effects and detailed data listings. I'm also planning `ToolInputGroup` for clean inputs, and `ToolOptionGrid` as interactive selectors. I plan to create `ToolSummaryCard`, `ToolEmptyState`, `ToolPreviewNotice`, and `ToolCTA` for UI completeness.\n\n\n**Finalizing Component Implementation**\n\nI'm now fully committed to the component implementation, including `ToolMotionReveal`, `ToolTabs`, `ToolComparisonRail`, and `ToolDataCard`. The list is exhaustive and covers all requirements. I've double-checked all exclusions. I'm ready to write clean, complete code with no placeholders, ensuring the /build pages are perfect.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T16:12:54.213Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"3b4kj1rb","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/components/build/types.ts","new_text":"export type Industry =\n  | \"banking\"\n  | \"insurance\"\n  | \"healthcare\"\n  | \"life-sciences\"\n  | \"retail\"\n  | \"manufacturing\"\n  | \"telecom\"\n  | \"energy\"\n  | \"mining\"\n  | \"public-sector\"\n  | \"education\"\n  | \"tax\"\n  | \"audit\"\n  | \"legal\"\n  | \"advisory\";\n\nexport type CompanySize = \"small\" | \"medium\" | \"enterprise\" | \"global-conglomerate\";\n\nexport type AIJourney =\n  | \"exploring\"  // Discovery phase\n  | \"piloting\"   // Integration setup\n  | \"scaling\"    // Deep orchestration\n  | \"optimized\"; // Continuous adaptation\n\nexport type DataReadiness = \"raw\" | \"structured\" | \"hybrid\" | \"vectorized\" | \"fully-governed\";\n\nexport type Priority =\n  | \"cost_reduction\"\n  | \"compliance_security\"\n  | \"operational_speed\"\n  | \"customer_experience\"\n  | \"decision_automation\";\n\nexport interface AssessmentAnswers {\n  dataIntegration: number;     // Range 1 to 5\n  vpcIsolation: number;        // Range 1 to 5\n  complianceTelemetry: number; // Range 1 to 5\n  fleetStrategy: number;       // Range 1 to 5\n  industry: Industry;\n}\n\nexport interface AssessmentResult {\n  score: number;\n  level: string;\n  color: string;\n  description: string;\n  dimensionScores: {\n    label: string;\n    score: number;\n    description: string;\n    recommendation: string;\n  }[];\n  strategicPriority: string;\n  securityClearance: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ROIInputs {\n  teamSize: number;\n  avgHourlyRate: number;\n  inefficientHoursPerWeek: number;\n  initialInvestment: number;\n  priority: Priority;\n}\n\nexport interface ROIResult {\n  annualHoursSaved: number;\n  grossSavings: number;\n  netSavings: number;\n  roiPercentage: number;\n  paybackMonths: number;\n  costAllocations: {\n    label: string;\n    percentage: number;\n    amount: number;\n    color: string;\n  }[];\n  efficiencyMultiplier: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ProposalInputs {\n  companyName: string;\n  industry: Industry;\n  companySize: CompanySize;\n  dataReadiness: DataReadiness;\n  priorities: Priority[];\n  budgetRange: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ProposalResult {\n  projectName: string;\n  implementationWeeks: number;\n  architecturePhases: {\n    name: string;\n    weeks: number;\n    objectives: string[];\n    deliverables: string[];\n  }[];\n  recommendedAgentTopologies: {\n    name: string;\n    role: string;\n    latency: string;\n    governanceMode: string;\n  }[];\n  estimatedLicenseCost: string;\n  exportOutline: string[];\n}\n\nexport interface SandboxAgent {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  role: string;\n  status: \"idle\" | \"running\" | \"completed\" | \"error\";\n  latency: string;\n  successRate: string;\n  steps: {\n    label: string;\n    status: \"pending\" | \"running\" | \"success\" | \"error\";\n    detail: string;\n  }[];\n}\n\nexport interface MarketplaceAgent {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  category: \"CONNECTOR\" | \"COGNITIVE_NODE\" | \"AUDITOR\" | \"SUPERVISOR\";\n  description: string;\n  compatibility: string[];\n  priceToken: string;\n  rating: number;\n  downloads: number;\n  badge?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface GeneratedReport {\n  id: string;\n  title: string;\n  timestamp: string;\n  type: \"roi\" | \"assessment\" | \"proposal\" | \"blueprint\";\n  summary: string;\n  score?: number;\n  savingsEstimate?: number;\n  recommendedSteps: string[];\n  metadata: Record<string, string | number | boolean>;\n}\n"}}}
